  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "First, make your pickles. Start by slicing the carrot and cucumber into small batons (sticks) with a knife or a julienne peeler. Slice one jalapeño thinly and save the other for garnish."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a small saucepan, add 240ml water, 240ml white vinegar, 1 tsp salt, 1 tbsp sugar, 1 tsp black peppercorns. Bring to a boil and then turn off the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the marinade, mince a thumb-sized piece of ginger and one or two garlic cloves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Then, whisk together 2 tbsp of olive oil, 3 tbsp tamari, the juice and zest of half a lime, the garlic and ginger, 2 tbsp of lemongrass paste and some black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add one 220g pack of Eatplanted Pulled Pork to the marinade and set aside to marinate while you make the rest of the fillings."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the paté, add the vegan 'pulled pork' protein to a blender with 85ml of water. Add 1tbsp soy sauce, 1 tsp miso, 2 tsp Moscatel or sherry vinegar, 1 stock cube and 2 tsp butter. Blend to a paté, season to taste and adjust the consistency with a little more water if you like."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Mix the mayonnaise with the sriracha in a small bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the remaining chilli, the spring onion and pick some coriander leaves for your garnish."
    }
  ],
